<title>USA: Verifone stock gains on stock buyback news.</title>
<headline>Verifone stock gains on stock buyback news.</headline>
<dateline>REDWOOD CITY, Calif.</dateline>
<text>
<p>The stock of VeriFone Inc. jumped Tuesday after the maker of electronic payment systems used by financial institutions and retailers said it planned to repurchase up to 1.5 million of its shares during the fourth quarter.</p>
<p>VeriFone was up $2.25 at $34.875 on the New York Stock Exchange in afternoon trading.</p>
<p>The company said it planned to spend up to $67.5 million to buy back the shares. During the first nine months of this year, VeriFone repurchased 995,000 shares for a total of $47.5 million. At the end of September, the company had 24.8 million shares outstanding.</p>
